        <Parent_String>creasing stakes [300023210], stakes (tools) [300023205], tools for forging and metal-shaping [300023117], equipment for forging and metal-shaping [300163316], metalworking equipment [300162819], equipment by material processed [300168082], equipment [300122241], Tools and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300022238], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>T-shaped creasing stakes having a different surface on each of the two arms. For example, one side of the T may be grooved or notched, while the other side may be flat or rounded.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000083291/Daugherty, Essentials of Sheet Metal Work (1918)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>T-vormige rilstokken met een verschillend oppervlak op elk van de twee armen. De ene arm van de T is bijvoorbeeld gegroefd of gekerfd, en de andere arm vlak of afgerond.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
